The hunting of polar bears is strictly regulated, with bans on hunting bear cubs and pregnant bears, as well as a seasonal ban from July to September.
Climate change has led to a decline in polar bear habitats, prompting calls for their protection as a threatened species.
Conservation groups have sued the government to address the impact of global warming on polar bears.
Despite opposition from some, listing polar bears as threatened under the Endangered Species Act is crucial for their survival.
The administration's acknowledgment of the effects of global warming on polar bears marks a significant shift in policy.
